FOR THE SENATE STATE AFFAIRS ENGROSSED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Aylward
1 An Act to amend the time required for filing a petition referring an ordinance or
2 resolution of a political subdivision modify the requirements to refer an
3 ordinance or resolution to the voters of a political subdivision.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
5 Section 1. That § 7-18A-8 be AMENDED:
6 7-18A-8. Except such resolutions or ordinances as may be necessary for the
7 immediate preservation of the public peace, health, or safety, or support of the county
8 government and its existing public institutions; which provide for an election or hearing
9 on an improvement or assessment; or which call for bids which take effect upon the
10 passage and publication thereof, every resolution or ordinance passed by a board shall
11 take effect on the twentieth day after its completed publication unless suspended by
12 operation of a referendum.
13 Except as otherwise provided in this section, an ordinance or resolution passed by
14 a board of county commissioners takes effect on the thirtieth twentieth day after the final
15 publication of the ordinance or resolution in the county's official newspapers, as designated
16 pursuant to § 7-18-3.
17 An ordinance or resolution takes effect upon the passage and publication of the
18 ordinance or resolution if the ordinance or resolution:
19 (1) May be necessary for:
20 (a) The immediate preservation of the public peace, health, or safety; or
21 (b) The support of the county government and its existing public institutions;
22 (2) Provides for an election;
23 (3) Provides for a hearing on an improvement or assessment; or
24 (4) Calls for a bid.
25 An ordinance or resolution that has been referred to a vote of the people does not
26 take effect until the completion of the referendum process.
