8 Section 8. That § 10-12-43 be AMENDED:
9 10-12-43. The governing body of the school district may raise additional revenues
10 for general fund purposes only, from property tax through the imposition of an excess tax
11 levy. The governing body of a school district may impose the excess tax levy with an
12 affirmative two-thirds vote of the governing body on or before July fifteenth of the year
13 prior to the year the taxes are payable. On any excess tax levy approved after July 1,
14 2002, the governing body of the taxing district shall specify in the resolution the year or
15 number of years the excess tax levy will be applied.
16 The requirements for an announcement made pursuant to this section are as
17 follows:
18 (1) The decision of the governing body to originally impose or subsequently
19 increase an excess tax levy shall be first published within ten days of the decision;
20 (2) Publication shall be made at least twice in the legal newspaper designated pursuant
21 to § 13-8-10, with no fewer than five days between publication dates, before the
22 opt out takes effect;
23 (3) The announcement shall be at least three newspaper columns in width and four
24 inches in length or at least one-sixth of a page in size, whichever size is greater;
25 (4) The announcement shall be headed with the following statement in a typeface no
26 less than eighteen point type: "ATTENTION TAXPAYERS: NOTICE OF PROPERTY
27 TAX INCREASE OF $(fill in amount)." The remainder of the announcement shall
28 consist of a reproduction of the "Resolution for Opt Out," including the amount that
29 property taxes will be increased annually by the proposed opt out and a statement
30 of the right to refer the decision of the board to a vote of the people as provided
31 in this section. The secretary of revenue, in rules promulgated pursuant to chapter
32 1-26, shall prescribe a uniform form to be used by the school district for notification
33 of taxpayers as required by this section. However, the requirements of subdivisions
34 (3) and (4) shall be waived if:
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

