10 The opt out decision may be referred to a vote of the people upon a resolution of
11 the governing body of the school district or by a petition signed by at least five percent of
12 the registered voters in the school district and filed with the governing body within twenty
13 days of the first publication of the decision. The referendum election shall be held on or
14 before October first of the year prior to the time the taxes are payable.
15 The board of a school district may, by resolution, impose an excess tax levy to
16 raise additional revenues from property tax for general fund purposes only. The board
17 may impose the excess tax levy with an affirmative vote of at least two-thirds of the
18 members on or before July fifteenth of the year prior to the year the taxes are payable.
19 The board shall specify in the resolution the year or number of years the excess tax is to
20 be applied.
21 The decision of the board to impose or increase an excess tax levy must first be
22 published in the district's legal newspaper, as designated pursuant to § 13-8-10, within
23 ten days of the board's decision. The board must publish at least two additional
24 notifications in the district's legal newspaper, the last of which must be published not more
25 than seven days before the excess levy takes effect, provided that there are at least five
26 days between the publication of the two notices. Each notice must:
27 (1) Contain the following headline in a typeface no less than eighteen-point type:
28 "ATTENTION TAXPAYERS: NOTICE OF PROPERTY TAX INCREASE OF $(fill in
29 amount)";
30 (2) Consist of a reproduction of the "Resolution for Opt Out," including the amount by
31 which property taxes are to be increased annually by the proposed opt out; and
32 (3) Include a statement of the right to refer the decision of the board to a vote of the
33 people, as provided in this section.
34 The board is not required to meet the formatting and content requirements
35 required by subdivisions (2) and (3) if the excess tax levy is for less than fifteen thousand
