19 Section 9. That § 10-12-43.1 be AMENDED:
20 10-12-43.1. A school district may raise additional revenues for capital outlay fund
21 purposes through the imposition of an excess tax levy. A school district seeking to impose
22 an excess tax levy pursuant to this section is subject to the same opt out procedures and
23 requirements as provided in § 10-12-43. The opt out decision may be referred to a vote
24 of the people in the same manner as provided in § 10-12-43.
25 A school district imposing an excess tax levy pursuant to this section shall exclude
26 any additional revenue generated by the excess tax levy from the total tax revenues
27 deposited in the capital outlay fund when calculating the maximum allowable transfer to
28 the school district's general fund authorized under § 13-16-6. Any additional Additional
29 revenue generated by the excess tax levy may only be used for capital outlay fund
30 purposes pursuant to § 13-16-6.
31 In no year may the annual tax levy for capital outlay fund purposes exceed the
32 levy authorized under § 13-16-7.
