1323G 17 1323
1 Section 20. That § 7-18A-15.1 be REPEALED.
2 Any legislative decision of a board of county commissioners is subject to the
3 referendum process. A legislative decision is one that enacts a permanent law or lays
4 down a rule of conduct or course of policy for the guidance of citizens or their officers. Any
5 matter of a permanent or general character is a legislative decision.
6 No administrative decision of a governing body is subject to the referendum
7 process, unless specifically authorized by this code. An administrative decision is one that
8 merely puts into execution a plan already adopted by the governing body itself or by the
9 Legislature. Supervision of a program is an administrative decision. Hiring, disciplining,
10 and setting the salaries of employees are administrative decisions.
11 Section 21. That § 7-18A-16 be REPEALED.
12 A petition to refer an ordinance or resolution subject to referendum may be filed
13 with the auditor within twenty days after publication of the ordinance or resolution in the
14 last to publish official county newspaper. The filing of the petition requires the submission
15 of the ordinance or resolution to a vote of the qualified voters of the county for rejection
16 or approval of the ordinance or resolution.
17 Section 22. That § 9-20-19 be REPEALED.
18 Any legislative decision of a governing body is subject to the referendum process.
19 A legislative decision is one that enacts a permanent law or lays down a rule of conduct
20 or course of policy for the guidance of citizens or their officers. Any matter of a permanent
21 or general character is a legislative decision.
22 No administrative decision of a governing body is subject to the referendum
23 process, unless specifically authorized by this code. An administrative decision is one that
24 merely puts into execution a plan already adopted by the governing body itself or by the
25 Legislature. Supervision of a program is an administrative decision. Hiring, disciplining,
26 and setting the salaries of employees are administrative decisions.
27 Section 23. That § 13-26-10 be REPEALED.
28 A petition to refer a school board decision may be filed with the business manager
29 of the school district within twenty days after its publication. The filing of the petition shall
30 require the submission of the decision to a vote of the qualified voters of the school district
31 for its rejection or approval.
